The paper introduces a new computational model for data streams and presents positive results for a series of important problems in the streaming literature. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
